sql:
SELECT AVG(issue_count) AS average_issue_count
FROM (
  SELECT project_id, COUNT(*) AS issue_count
  FROM issues
  GROUP BY project_id
) AS project_issues;

SELECT issue_id
FROM issues
WHERE number_of_comments > (SELECT AVG(number_of_comments) FROM issues);

SELECT milestone_title, status
FROM milestones
WHERE status = 'open';

external_knowledge:
Project activity can be quantified by the number of issues or pull requests and the average number of comments, which reflects the level of engagement or discussion around each issue or pull request. Higher numbers typically indicate more active projects.;
The term "project" refers to distinct software development projects identified by a unique project ID.;
"Discussion levels" in this context refer to the average number of comments on issues or pull requests, indicating the amount of conversation or feedback on those topics.;
